[@ev](@8Qee0I/DwI5DHSCi3p5fsl6FyLGArrnDz3ox9qZr5Qc=.ed25519)

You could remove the `master` plugin, but I think at a bare minimum you'd need one that looks like this:

```js
module.exports = function (api, opts) {
  // main identity stored in `~/.ssb/secret`
  const mainIdentity = api.id

  api.auth.hook(function (fn, args) {
    // authenticate id connecting via muxrpc

    const id = args[0]
    const cb = args[1]

    if (id === mainIdentity) {
      // id is allowed to do anything 
      cb(null, {allow: null, deny: null})
    } else {
      // id is allowed to do nothing
      cb(null, null)
    }
  })
}
```

This would give the same effect without adding a hook to allow identifiers from `opts.master` as well. I think that by default *no identifiers* are allowed to make calls to ssb-server, so this plugin exists to whitelist the identity that we're using.
